2. **Clear**: The "Clear" button resets the canvas, removing all drawings.
3. **Send**: Clicking the "Send" button generates the HTML content reflecting your drawing and copies it to your clipboard.

### Usage Instructions:
1. **Draw**: Use your mouse to draw on the canvas.
2. **Clear**: Click the "Clear" button to erase your drawing.
3. **Send**: Click "Send" to copy the HTML representation of your drawing to the clipboard. You can then create a new HTML file, paste the copied content, and see your drawing displayed.

This implementation ensures that the drawing feels responsive and that the generated HTML is correct and free of bugs. Enjoy your drawing app!

Hereâ€™s an advanced implementation of a drawing app that allows users to select paint colors and brush widths, draw on an HTML canvas, and then generate a new HTML page with their drawing when clicking the "Send" button.

Copy and paste the code below into an HTML file (like `draw-app.html`) and open it in your web browser:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Canvas Drawing App</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        canvas {
            border: 1px solid #000;
            cursor: crosshair;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
        #controls {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        input[type="color"], input[type="range"] {
            margin: 5px;
        }
        button {
            margin: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Canvas Drawing App</h1>
<div id="controls">
    <label for="colorPicker">Color:</label>
    <input type="color" id="colorPicker" value="#000000">

    <label for="brushWidth">Brush Width:</label>
    <input type="range" id="brushWidth" min="1" max="20" value="5">
</div>
<canvas id="drawCanvas" width="500" height="400"></canvas><br>
<button id="clearBtn">Clear</button>
<button id="sendBtn">Send</button>

<script>
    const canvas = document.getElementById('drawCanvas');
    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
    const colorPicker = document.getElementById('colorPicker');
    const brushWidth = document.getElementById('brushWidth');

    let drawing = false;

    // Set initial brush settings
    ctx.lineWidth = brushWidth.value;
    ctx.strokeStyle = colorPicker.value;

    // Event handlers for drawing
    function startPosition(e) {
        drawing = true;
        draw(e);
    }

    function endPosition() {
        drawing = false;
        ctx.beginPath();
    }

    function draw(e) {
        if (!drawing) return;

        ctx.lineWidth = brushWidth.value;
        ctx.strokeStyle = colorPicker.value;

        ctx.lineTo(e.offsetX, e.offsetY);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(e.offsetX, e.offsetY);
    }

    canvas.addEventListener('mousedown', startPosition);
    canvas.addEventListener('mouseup', endPosition);
    canvas.addEventListener('mousemove', draw);
    canvas.addEventListener('mouseleave', endPosition);

    // Clear button functionality
    document.getElementById('clearBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {
        ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
    });

    // Send button functionality
    document.getElementById('sendBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {
        const dataURL = canvas.toDataURL();

        const htmlContent = `
            <!DOCTYPE html>
            <html lang="en">
            <head>
                <meta charset="UTF-8">
                <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
                <title>My Drawing</title>
                <style>
                    body {
                        display: flex;
                        justify-content: center;
                        align-items: center;
                        height: 100vh;
                        background-color: #f0f0f0;
                    }
                    canvas {
                        border: 1px solid #000;
                    }
                </style>
            </head>
            <body>
                <h1>My Drawing</h1>
                <canvas id="drawCanvas" width="500" height="400"></canvas>
                <script>
                    const canvas = document.getElementById('drawCanvas');
                    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
                    const img = new Image();
                    img.src = '${dataURL}';
                    img.onload = () => {
                        ctx.drawImage(img, 0, 0);
                    };
                </script>
            </body>
            </html>
        `;

        // Create a Blob from the HTML content and open it in a new window
        const blob = new Blob([htmlContent], { type: 'text/html' });
        const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
        window.open(url);
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Features:
1. **Drawing**: Users can draw on the canvas with a selected color and brush width.
2. **Color Picker**: A color input allows users to select their desired drawing color.
3. **Brush Width Control**: A range input to adjust the brush width dynamically.
4. **Canvas**: A canvas where users can draw their artwork.
5. **Clear Button**: A button to clear the canvas.
6. **Send Button**: This creates an HTML page from the drawing and opens it in a new tab.

### Usage Instructions:
1. **Select Color**: Choose your preferred color using the color picker.
2. **Adjust Brush Width**: Use the slider to set the thickness of the brush.
3. **Draw**: Click and drag on the canvas to create your drawing.
4. **Clear Canvas**: Click the "Clear" button to erase the drawing.
5. **Send Drawing**: Click the "Send" button to generate an HTML page with your drawing, which will automatically open in a new tab.

This implementation ensures a smooth user experience while providing the requested functionalities. Enjoy your drawing app!
